description:
**Problem:** All links underline on hover uniformly. This is safe but could be more refined.

**Design Issue:** Link styling contributes to overall polish. Uniform underlines feel dated.

**Recommendation:**
- Use color change only for navigation links (no underline)
- Add animated underline for content links (grow from left)
- Consider underline offset for better typography
- Different styles for different link contexts

**Specific Styles:**
- Navigation: Color change only, no underline
- In-content links: Animated underline (transition: transform)
- Footer links: Subtle opacity change
- CTAs: Button styling (already done)

**Technical Approach:**
```css
/* Animated underline */
a {
  text-decoration: none;
  background: linear-gradient(currentColor, currentColor);
  background-size: 0% 1px;
  background-position: left bottom;
  transition: background-size 0.2s;
}
a:hover {
  background-size: 100% 1px;
}
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Link styling feels intentional and refined
- [ ] Different contexts have appropriate styles
- [ ] Hover states are smooth (transitions)
- [ ] Links remain clearly identifiable as links
- [ ] Accessible focus states maintained
